The paper discusses the design of hybrid precoding for millimeter wave (mm-wave) communications, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The proposed dynamic mapping algorithm also involves system-level optimization (cs.SY). The use of mm-wave technology and antenna design is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and augmented reality (cs.AR) applications.
